projects.description:
Dutch Railways has decided to upgrade their current "Plato" environment to CSC's latest "Dynamic Desktop" solution in preparation for a standardized future workplace. This program is responsible for ensuring that the first business unit "NedTrain" is migrated to a new Microsoft Windows 7 based environment. 

As Transition Manager within this Transition & Transformation project, I am responsible for: 

- Coordinating the implementation and configuration of the dynamic desktop back end;
- Clients application portfolio is rationalized to approximately 250 applications;
- Applications are packaged or streamed;
- Upgrade existing Microsoft Exchange environment and migrate users to the new environment;
- Implement Sharepoint solution;
- Implement new data structure and migrate fileservers to new environment;
- Implement Enterprise Service Management;
- Implement Service Desk Online.

Where required by the business I help to define the best possible approaches and solutions to perform assessments which allows them to deliver to the nescaserry details on users, applications and hardware. I manage a team consisting of approximately 50 FTE's. Apart from the main project deliverables I have set up a process of continuous improvement that leads to an increasingly optimized approach for the Application Publication Department, together with well documented and reusable processes for providing and maintaining clear overviews on status, progress, assigned tasks and use repetitive processes and procedures on both a technical and project management layer. This ensures a smooth transition of 2500 users and a total of 3500 seats to the new environment. The project team's ability to handle large volumes of work within very aggressive timescales grew significantly during a short period.
